<p class="mt-3">
    Modals are opened imperatively through <code>IModalService.ShowAsync&lt;TComponent, TResult&gt;</code>,
    which renders any component as the dialog body. A body declares the type it resolves with by
    inheriting <code>HBModal&lt;TResult&gt;</code> - that base satisfies the
    <code>IModalComponent&lt;TResult&gt;</code> contract and exposes <code>CloseAsync(result)</code>
    and <code>CancelAsync()</code> directly, so no cascading parameter or wiring is needed. For a
    simple confirm dialog, inherit the non-generic <code>HBModal</code> (a <code>bool</code> result)
    and call the parameterless <code>CloseAsync()</code> to confirm.
</p>

